        {
          "ruleId": "MASS-ASSIGNMENT",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "The POST /benefits handler extracts userId and benefitStartDate directly from req.body without authorization checks (any authenticated user can modify any other user's benefits). The userId is passed to parseInt() then used as a MongoDB _id filter, and benefitStartDate is written directly to the database without sanitization or format validation. Combined with the missing isAdmin check, this allows any authenticated user to modify arbitrary users' benefit records."
          },
